<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 8:54PM EST  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Mason
and central Jackson Counties through 930 PM EST...
At 854 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Ripley, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Fairplain, Evans and Given.
This includes Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 130
and 140.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
